				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I read a comment here which I thought was incredibly studpid. I'll tell you what I mean. First of all this is an RPG, that means you take the role of another player, and you decide what this character does. And with these decisions the character earns exp., money, items, faction or anything else.<BR>
So when this guy said that I earned the money I should do whatever I want to do with it. He used this argument to say that the money should still be droppable so he could pick it up with another one of his characters. Well, this is an RPG!! When you start a new character, this character is in no way related to whoever other characters you have in this game.<BR>
If we should take your argument one step further we could say: &quot;well, since I've gotten so good faction with my warrior, why can't I take some of it and give it to this new character I am going to start playing.&quot; It is exactly the same thing. And I hope all RPGers see my point here.<BR>
<BR>
Verant, it is a good idea! But there is one drawback with it, PCs can never make quests for newbies that includes them to find some money you dropped. That is a little shame....
				</font>
